<s> external trade statistics by mode of transport in first half 1997 </s>
<s> the value of hong_kong 's external trade by ocean accounted for 47 % of hong_kong 's total value of external trade in the first half of 1997 , according to statistics released by the census and statistics department today ( tuesday ) . </s>
<s> another 25 % was transported by land , another 21 % by air and the remaining 6.0 % included shipment by river , postal parcels and accompanied goods of passengers travelling on various means of transport . </s>
<s> shipment by ocean amounted to $ 682.6 billion in the first half of 1997 , representing an increase of 1.2 % over that in the same period in 1996 . </s>
<s> shipment by land went up by 3.6 % to $ 361.9 billion in the first half of 1997 while that by air rose by 9.7 % to $ 307.5 billion . </s>
<s> the united_states remained the largest destination for hong_kong 's total exports ( comprising domestic exports and re @-@ exports ) by ocean , </s>
<s> accounting for a share of 31 % in value terms in the first half of 1997 . </s>
<s> the value of total exports by ocean to the united_states went up by 6.3 % in the first half of 1997 over a year earlier . </s>
<s> comparing the first half of 1997 with the same period in 1996 , </s>
<s> increases were also recorded in the value of seaborne total exports to the mainland of china ( the mainland ) ( + 11 % ) and the united kingdom ( + 1.4 % ) . </s>
<s> however , the value of total exports by ocean to germany and japan decreased by 7.9 % and 4.6 % respectively . </s>
<s> japan was the largest supplier of hong_kong 's imports by ocean , accounting for a share of 22 % in the first half of 1997 . </s>
<s> the value , however , decreased by 0.8 % over the same period in 1996 . </s>
<s> the value of seaborne imports from taiwan and south korea also decreased , by 6.3 % and 2.5 % respectively in the first half of 1997 . </s>
<s> comparing the first half of 1997 with the same period in 1996 , the value of seaborne imports from the mainland and the united_states increased by 5.1 % and 1.6 % respectively . </s>
<s> in the first half of 1997 , the value of total exports by air to the united_states accounted for 26 % of the value of hong_kong 's total exports by air and increased by 14 % over the same period in 1996 . </s>
<s> the value of total exports by air to taiwan , germany and japan also increased by 13 % , 4.9 % and 4.6 % respectively over the same period in 1996 . </s>
<s> however , the value of airborne total exports to singapore decreased by 4.1 % . </s>
<s> in the first half of 1997 , increases were recorded in the value of imports by air from the main suppliers : </s>
<s> the united kingdom ( + 28 % ) , japan ( + 19 % ) , </s>
<s> taiwan ( + 16 % ) , singapore ( + 11 % ) and the united_states ( + 3.2 % ) . </s>
<s> comparing the first half of 1997 with the same period in 1996 , increases were recorded in the value of re @-@ exports by ocean for clothing ( by $ 3.6 billion or 11 % ) ; </s>
<s> miscellaneous manufactured articles consisting mainly of baby carriages , toys , games and sporting goods ( by $ 1.8 billion or 3.3 % ) ; </s>
<s> footwear ( by $ 1.4 billion or 4.9 % ) ; </s>
<s> and electrical machinery , apparatus and appliances , and electrical parts thereof ( by $ 1.2 billion or 5.1 % ) . </s>
<s> however , </s>
<s> a decrease was recorded in the value of re @-@ exports by ocean for telecommunications and sound recording and reproducing apparatus and equipment ( by $ 2.4 billion or 6.4 % ) . </s>
<s> the value of domestic exports by ocean for most of the principal commodity divisions fell in the first half of 1997 , </s>
<s> with a more notable decrease for clothing ( by $ 990 million or 5.2 % ) . </s>
<s> however , </s>
<s> a marginal increase was recorded in the value of domestic exports by ocean for office machines and automatic data processing machines ( by $ 2 million or 0.1 % ) . </s>
<s> over the same period , </s>
<s> increases were recorded in the value of imports by ocean for road vehicles ( by $ 2.1 billion or 11 % ) ; </s>
<s> and electrical machinery , apparatus and appliances , and electrical parts thereof ( by $ 1.9 billion or 8.5 % ) . </s>
<s> on the other hand , </s>
<s> decreases were recorded in the value of imports by ocean for telecommunications , sound recording , reproducing apparatus and equipment ( by $ 3.2 billion or 13 % ) ; </s>
<s> plastics in primary forms ( by $ 1.5 billion or 8.1 % ) ; </s>
<s> and textiles ( by $ 1.1 billion or 2.5 % ) . </s>
<s> comparing the first half of 1997 with the same period in 1996 , increases were recorded in the value of re @-@ exports by air for all the principal commodity divisions . </s>
<s> more significant increases were recorded for office machines and automatic data processing machines ( by $ 2.4 billion or 18 % ) ; </s>
<s> as well as electrical machinery , apparatus and appliances , and electrical parts thereof ( by $ 2.0 billion or 10 % ) . </s>
<s> an increase was recorded in the value of domestic exports by air for electrical machinery , apparatus and appliances , and electrical parts thereof ( by $ 1.0 billion or 9.3 % ) . </s>
<s> however , significant decreases were recorded in the value of domestic exports by air for office machines and automatic data processing machines ( by $ 1.0 billion or 29 % ) ; </s>
<s> and clothing ( by $ 766 million or 11 % ) . </s>
<s> over the same period , </s>
<s> more significant increases were recorded in the value of imports by air for telecommunications , sound recording , reproducing apparatus and equipment ( by $ 7.5 billion or 40 % ) ; </s>
<s> office machines and automatic data processing machines ( by $ 6.1 billion or 38 % ) ; </s>
<s> and electrical machinery , apparatus and appliances , and electrical parts thereof ( by $ 5.2 billion or 10 % ) . </s>
<s> meanwhile , </s>
<s> a decrease was recorded in the value of imports by air for photographic apparatus , equipment and supplies , optical goods , </s>
<s> watches and clocks ( by $ 503 million or 3.9 % ) . </s>
<s> comparing the first half of 1997 with the same period in 1996 , more notable increases were recorded in the value of re @-@ exports by land for electrical machinery , apparatus and appliances , </s>
<s> and electrical parts thereof ( by $ 1.3 billion or 12 % ) ; </s>
<s> and textiles ( by $ 1.3 billion or 4.1 % ) . </s>
<s> however , decreases were recorded in the value of re @-@ exports by land for telecommunications , sound recording and reproducing apparatus and equipment ( by $ 552 million or 7.7 % ) ; </s>
<s> and plastics in primary forms ( by $ 122 million or 1.2 % ) . </s>
<s> a more notable increase was recorded in the value of domestic exports by land for clothing ( by $ 1.5 billion or 54 % ) in the first half of 1997 . </s>
<s> however , decreases were recorded in the value of domestic exports by land for electrical machinery , apparatus and appliances , </s>
<s> and electrical parts thereof ( by $ 168 million or 7.1 % ) ; </s>
<s> and miscellaneous manufactured articles consisting mainly of baby carriages , toys , games and sporting goods ( by $ 135 million or 8.2 % ) . </s>
<s> over the same period , </s>
<s> increases were recorded in the value of imports by land for clothing ( by $ 6.1 billion or 17 % ) ; </s>
<s> electrical machinery , apparatus and appliances , and electrical parts thereof ( by $ 1.4 billion or 7.7 % ) ; </s>
<s> miscellaneous manufactured articles consisting mainly of baby carriages , toys , games and sporting goods ( by $ 1.1 billion or 3.7 % ) ; </s>
<s> and footwear ( by $ 699 million or 3.2 % ) . </s>
<s> but a decrease was recorded in the value of imports by land for telecommunications , sound recording and reproducing apparatus and equipment ( by $ 1.1 billion or 4.7 % ) . </s>
